<div class="container">

  <h1>Secure WordPress wp-admin Folder</h1>
  <p style="text-align:center; color:#555;">Add an extra password layer to protect your WordPress admin panel.</p>

  <div class="box">
    <h2>Step 1: Create .htpasswd File</h2>
    <p>Login to cPanel and go to your WordPress root directory. Create a file named <code>.htpasswd</code> and add:</p>
    <pre><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>username:password</pre>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <h2>Step 2: Find the Full File Path</h2>
    <p>Create a file named <code>test.php</code> in the same folder, add this code:</p>
    <pre><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>&lt;?php
echo dirname(__FILE__) . '/.htpasswd';
?&gt;</pre>
    <p>Open it in browser:</p>
    <pre><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>https://yourdomain.com/test.php</pre>
    <p>Copy the path displayed, then delete <code>test.php</code>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <h2>Step 3: Protect wp-admin</h2>
    <p>In <code>wp-admin</code> folder create <code>.htaccess</code> file and paste:</p>
    <pre><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>AuthType Basic
AuthName "Restricted Area"
AuthUserFile /path/to/.htpasswd
Require valid-user</pre>
    <p>Replace <code>/path/to/.htpasswd</code> with the copied path.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="done">
    <h2>âœ” Setup Complete</h2>
    <p>Your wp-admin is now protected with an additional login layer.</p>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
  function copyCode(btn) {
    const code = btn.parentElement.innerText.replace("Copy","").trim();
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(code);
    btn.innerText = "Copied!";
    setTimeout(()=> btn.innerText = "Copy", 1500);
  }
</script>

